ðŸ” Shallow Copy:
Copies only the first level. Nested objects still share references.
	âœ… Shallow Copy Methods:
	- Object.assign({}, obj)
	- Spread syntax: { ...obj } or [...arr]
	- Array.prototype.slice()

ðŸ§  Deep Copy:
Copies all nested levels, recursively.
	Deep Copy Methods:
	- JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj) â†’ works for JSON-safe objects only --> does not work with functions, `undefined`, etc.
	- structuredClone(obj) â†’ native, supports most types (âœ… better choice)
	- Libraries like lodash.cloneDeep()


