Higher Order Function â€”> function that takes another function as input parameter or returns any function. 
	x(function y () {console.log(â€œhelloâ€)}); â€”> In this example y is first class function and x is high order function. 
Parameter â€”> placeholder for value passed in function declaration
Argument â€”> value passed when function is called 
Arrow function â€”> Introduced in ES6 â€” shorter function syntax that also does not have its own this, arguments, or prototype.
